metadata.proposal_title: Large Language Models for Wireless Communications

form_data.observations:
There are no third-party software packages listed in the proposal. They only mention using tools like NVIDIA Sionna and Wireless InSite.

No specific dataset names are provided in the proposal.
What they say they will use instead:
A generated large-scale ray-tracing dataset of wireless propagation/channel data (they plan to generate it during the project) 
“Data Readiness” section dataset entries are TBD (not filled)

Self-development of models have been identified however, no indication of any prior effort toward model development is evident in the proposal
form_data.recommendation: Recommended for Ibex use for maturity.
